2. He ſaith the Iſraelites were confined to Gods Altar in a certain place;
               Page 45. and Mr. Crofton ſaith Chriſtians are confined to Gods worſhip in certain aſſemblies; true conſtituted Churches, ſuch as our Antagoniſt yieldeth Englands Congregations to be; Mr. Crofton denieth not local liberty, or the place of worſhip to be the matter of indifferencie; the man is miſtaken, locallity never became a Topick of any force to Mr. Crofton he ſaith to a true Church, a lawfully conſtituted Chriſtian aſſembly, meet, aſſemble where you will and can, that which he ſaith againſt the looſe affections of ſome Chriſtians, apt to wander, is, forſake not the Aſſembling of your ſelves together, as the manner of ſome is: let Chriſts flock lie where it will or can, all particular members muſt keep Company with them; and have good reaſon before they refuſe it; Chriſts true aſſemblies

 are to Chriſtians, what the fixed place, and altar was to the Jews.
